# Network Interfaces

Two network interfaces were configured.

| Interface | Purpose |
|-----------|----------|
| WAN | External network connectivity (Bridged Adapter) |
| LAN | Internal isolated enterprise network |

![Network Interfaces](../Screenshots/06-Network-Interfaces.png)

---

# WAN Configuration

The WAN interface is configured using a **Bridged Adapter** connected to the host's physical network.

Characteristics:

- DHCP Address Assignment
- Internet Connectivity
- OpenVPN Endpoint
- Receives traffic from external networks

---

# LAN Configuration

The LAN interface provides the isolated internal network used by all enterprise virtual machines.

Characteristics:

- Static IPv4 Address
- Internal Enterprise Network
- Default Gateway for Domain Clients
- Routing between internal hosts and external networks

Windows Server clients use this interface as their default gateway.

---

# IPv6 Configuration

IPv6 was intentionally disabled throughout the laboratory.

This project focuses on IPv4 enterprise networking, Active Directory integration, and security monitoring.

Disabling IPv6:

- Simplifies network management
- Prevents unused protocols from introducing additional attack surface
- Avoids accidental IPv6 communication bypassing IPv4 firewall policies
- Keeps the environment focused on enterprise IPv4 deployments

---

# DNS and DHCP Architecture

Unlike traditional pfSense deployments, this laboratory centralizes infrastructure services on **Windows Server**.

The Windows Server provides:

- Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)
- DNS Server
- DHCP Server
- Group Policy Objects (GPOs)

All domain clients receive their IP configuration and DNS information directly from Windows Server.

pfSense remains responsible only for:

- Layer 3 routing
- Gateway services
- NAT
- Firewall enforcement
- Secure external connectivity

---

# Firewall Rules

Firewall rules were configured following the principle of least privilege.

Only the required traffic is permitted while all other unsolicited inbound traffic remains blocked.

---

